# Doskvol

"The Dark Jewel of [[Akoros]]" — City Guide, p. 237+.

Established 1000+ years ago as a coal mining settlement on the cold north coast of Akoros. Has survived the cataclysm, a leviathan attack, massive fires, a plague, a civil war, and legions of angry ghosts. "A community of survivors."

Densely packed inside a ring of immense lightning towers that keep out the murderous ghosts of the deathlands beyond. Canals carry most goods and passengers. Its port launches the leviathan hunter fleet — leviathan blood is refined into electroplasm, the power source of civilization (p. 237).

## Names (p. 239)

- **Doskvol** — original, from old Skovic *do'skov'ol*, "the Skov's coal mine"
- **North Hook** — Imperial nautical designation
- **Duskwall** — modern Akorosian slang
- **"The Dusk"** — underworld slang

## History highlights (p. 238)

- ~160 PC: founded by the old Skov kingdom
- 551 IE: first leviathan blood harvested and refined
- 556 IE: first prototype lightning towers built around future Charterhall
- 809–845 IE: Unity War; thousands of Skovlander refugees arrive
- 847 IE: present day

## People (p. 239)

Heritage mix: Akorosi (most common), Skovlanders (working-class refugees, often mistreated), Iruvians (wealthy, influential consulate). Languages: Akorosian/"Imperial" (common tongue), Skovic, Hadrathi (rare).

## Daily life

- Three seasons: frigid winter, rainy spring, stormy fall; "hunting season" = 80% of leviathan hauls (p. 245)
- Staple cheap food: eel and mushroom pie (p. 246)

## Districts (pp. 256–278)

Barrowcleft, [[Brightstone]], Charhollow, Charterhall, Coalridge, Crow's Foot, the Docks, Dunslough, Nightmarket, [[Silkshore]], Six Towers, Whitecrown
